<% content_for :title, "Privacy Policy — recuerd0" %>
<% content_for :description, "How recuerd0 handles your data. No tracking, no third-party analytics, self-host option for full data sovereignty." %>
<% content_for :canonical_url, "https://recuerd0.ai/privacy" %>

<div data-controller="marketing-nav">

  <%= render "pages/marketing_nav" %>

  <main class="legal-content">
    <%= render "pages/legal_header", title: "Privacy Policy", date_label: "February 2026", date_iso: "2026-02" %>

    <nav class="legal-toc" aria-label="Sections">
      <p class="legal-toc-label">On this page</p>
      <ol>
        <li><a href="#information-collected">Information we collect</a></li>
        <li><a href="#how-we-use">How we use your information</a></li>
        <li><a href="#what-we-dont-do">What we don't do</a></li>
        <li><a href="#security">Data storage and security</a></li>
        <li><a href="#your-rights">Your rights</a></li>
        <li><a href="#retention">Data retention</a></li>
        <li><a href="#cookies">Cookies</a></li>
        <li><a href="#policy-changes">Changes to this policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <div class="legal-body">
      <h2 id="information-collected">1. Information we collect</h2>
      <p>We collect only what we need to provide the service:</p>
      <dl>
        <div><dt>Account information:</dt> <dd>your email address and a hashed password (we never store your password in plain text)</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Content you create:</dt> <dd>workspaces, memories, versions, and tags</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Session data:</dt> <dd>IP address and user agent for active sessions, used only for security purposes</dd></div>
      </dl>

      <h2 id="how-we-use">2. How we use your information</h2>
      <p>Your data is used exclusively to operate the recuerd0 service:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>To authenticate you and maintain your session</li>
        <li>To store and serve your workspaces and memories</li>
        <li>To send you service-related emails (password resets, account notifications)</li>
        <li>To detect and prevent unauthorized access</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="what-we-dont-do">3. What we don't do</h2>
      <p>We believe your data is yours. We commit to these principles:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>We <strong>do not sell</strong> your data to anyone, for any reason</li>
        <li>We <strong>do not share</strong> your data with third parties for marketing, advertising, or analytics</li>
        <li>We <strong>do not use</strong> your data to train AI or machine learning models — not ours, not anyone else's</li>
        <li>We <strong>do not track</strong> you across websites or services</li>
        <li>We <strong>do not display</strong> ads or engage in behavioral targeting</li>
        <li>We <strong>do not use</strong> third-party analytics, tracking pixels, or social media integrations</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="security">4. Data storage and security</h2>
      <p>Passwords are hashed using bcrypt. API access tokens are stored as SHA-256 hashes and the raw token is shown only once at creation. Sensitive credentials are never stored in plain text. Sessions use signed, HTTP-only cookies. We use HTTPS for all connections.</p>

      <h2 id="your-rights">5. Your rights</h2>
      <p>You have full control over your data:</p>
      <dl>
        <div><dt>Access:</dt> <dd>view all your data through the application or API</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Export:</dt> <dd>download your data via the API at any time</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Correction:</dt> <dd>edit or update any of your content</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Deletion:</dt> <dd>delete individual memories, workspaces, or your entire account</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Portability:</dt> <dd>your data is stored in standard formats and accessible via API</dd></div>
      </dl>
      <p>If you're in a region with statutory data-protection rights — such as the EU, UK, or California — these rights are yours to exercise at any time, and you may also lodge a complaint with your local data-protection authority.</p>

      <h2 id="retention">6. Data retention</h2>
      <dl>
        <div><dt>Active data:</dt> <dd>retained as long as your account exists</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Deleted workspaces:</dt> <dd>soft-deleted with a 30-day recovery window, then permanently removed</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Deleted memories:</dt> <dd>permanently removed immediately</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Account deletion:</dt> <dd>all data permanently removed upon account closure</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Session data:</dt> <dd>automatically cleaned up when sessions expire</dd></div>
      </dl>

      <h2 id="cookies">7. Cookies</h2>
      <p>We use only essential cookies:</p>
      <dl>
        <div><dt>Session cookie:</dt> <dd>a signed, HTTP-only cookie to maintain your login session</dd></div>
        <div><dt>UI preference cookie:</dt> <dd>remembers your sidebar state (open/closed)</dd></div>
      </dl>
      <p>We do not use third-party cookies, tracking cookies, or advertising cookies.</p>

      <h2 id="policy-changes">8. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>If we change this policy, we will notify you by email or through the application before the changes take effect. The "last updated" date at the top reflects the most recent revision.</p>

      <h2 id="contact">9. Contact</h2>
      <p>recuerd0 is operated by the recuerd0 team. For questions about this policy — or to access, export, or delete your data — reach out at <a href="mailto:info@recuerd0.ai">info@recuerd0.ai</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <%= render "pages/marketing_footer" %>

</div>
